        action serveLiveCache; // D0094: content-hash view cache (perf/pre-load) + SSE change-push (event-driven, not polling).
        verification serveLiveCacheDoD : Test { :>> id = "a1c70094-0094-4494-9494-516273840494"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "D0094 perf+events: a content FINGERPRINT (path+len+mtime over .tracking + .engine .sysml) drives (a) a per-view JSON cache keyed by fingerprint — recompute a view ONLY when the model changes (kills the per-request ~2s on unchanged data; warms via frontend pre-load); (b) GET /api/events SSE that polls the fingerprint server-side (~1.5s) and pushes `changed` ONLY when it flips, so the UI refetches EVENT-DRIVEN, not on a blind timer (hash unchanged => files unchanged; catches out-of-purview edits). A materialized #View cache (regenerable, section-2.1). Request log also appended to keel-serve.log. VERIFY (live): orient cold ~2s -> warm ~0.1s; /api/events emits hello/ping then `changed` on a file touch; keel-serve.log written; clippy + cargo test + keel validate + guard all green."; }
